\par\pard\plain \fi288\sb240\sl480\slmult1\ql\ltrch\loch {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 <$Scr_Ps::0>Shit, what have I done, she thought, walking back from her little hidey hole. He\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8217\'92s a good kid, I like him, and it was a fun, sweet romp. A bit more actually \hich\f1 \emdash \loch\f1  they had connected there for a while. But shit is already too complicated. Is he going to want to come with me when I go? Do I want him to?}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Her mind buzzed: And what if he doesn\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8217\'92t, and my feelings for him get more intense? I\u8217\'92ll hate him for making me stay. I have to avoid these moments of opening myself up, she thought, it will only put me in danger. No, that\u8217\'92s not right, either, she argued with herself. What\u8217\'92s the point of having empathic skills if I can\u8217\'92t be an empath, either to myself or him? }
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Maybe she\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8217\'92d try to find REM and ask him how he dealt with these moments. Or would he just think she\u8217\'92s a silly teenage girl? He\u8217\'92s old enough to be my grandfather, for fuck\u8217\'92s sake, she thought.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0 Her face was still flushed from sex, and the night air felt cool against it. It was too much to figure out now and she just let the heat and the coolness mix, feeling like somehow it was a metaphor for something. The answer would come, in time.<!$Scr_Ps::0>}}